that have been reported on ProMED-mail. The postings can be directly
accessed through this map.

References
----------
1. Zinkaa B, Raucha E, Buettnera A, Rueffb F, and Penninga R:
Unexplained cases of sudden infant death shortly after hexavalent
vaccination. Vaccine. 2006 26 Jul; 24(31-32): 5779-5780.

2. von Kries R, Toschke AM, Strassburger K, Kundi M, Kalies H,
Nennstiel U, Jorch G, Rosenbauer J, Giani G: Sudden and unexpected
deaths after the administration of hexavalent vaccines (diphtheria,
tetanus, pertussis, poliomyelitis, hepatitis B, _Haemophilius
influenzae_ type b): is there a signal? Eur J Pediatr. 2005 Feb;
164(2): 61-9. Epub 2004 Dec 16.

3. Balci Y, Tok M, Kocaturk BK, Yenilmez C, Yirulmaz C: Simultaneous
sudden infant death syndrome. J Forensic Leg Med. 2007 Feb; 14(2): 87-91.

4. DiMiceli L, Pool V, Kelso JM, Shadomy SV, Iskander J; VAERS Team:
Vaccination of yeast sensitive individuals: review of safety data in
the US vaccine adverse event reporting system (VAERS). Vaccine. 2006
Feb 6; 24(6):703-7. Epub 2005 Aug 9.

5. Eriksen EM, Perlman JA, Miller A, Marcy SM, Lee H, Vadheim C,
Zangwill KM, Chen RT, DeStefano F, Lewis E, Black S, Shinefield H,
Ward JI: Lack of association between hepatitis B birth immunization
and neonatal death: a population-based study from the vaccine safety
datalink project. Pediatr Infect Dis J. 2004 Jul; 23(7): 656-62.

6. Stratton K, Almario DA, Wizemann TM, McCormick MC, Immunization
Safety Review Committee: Immunization Safety Review: Vaccinations and
Sudden Unexpected Death in Infancy Executive summary available at
<http://www.nap.edu/catalog/10649.html>. The whole document is
available at no cost at <http://www.iom.edu/CMS/28693.aspx>.
- Mod.MPP]
